            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EKing%20Ahaz%20learned%20an%20important%20lesson%20in%20dealing%20with%20an%20attack%20of%20the%20enemy%3A%20you%20cannot%20run%20from%20the%20battle!%20When%20an%20army%20far%20superior%20to%20his%20own%20threatened%20Jerusalem%2C%20%22the%20hearts%20of%20the%20king%20and%20his%20people%20trembled%20with%20fear%2C%20just%20as%20trees%20shake%20in%20a%20storm%22%20(Isaiah%207%3A2).%20But%20God%20in%20His%20mercy%20sent%20the%20prophet%20Isaiah%20to%20deliver%20an%20encouraging%20message.%20Through%20Isaiah%20God%20told%20Ahaz%2C%20%22This%20invasion%20will%20never%20happen%22%20(v.%207)%2C%20and%20He%20further%20instructed%20the%20king%2C%20saying%2C%20%22If%20you%20want%20me%20to%20protect%20you%2C%20learn%20to%20believe%20what%20I%20say%22%20(v.%209).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20enemy's%20primary%20weapon%20is%20fear.%20When%20disaster%20loomed%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20Ahaz%20was%20overcome%20by%20fear%2C%20but%20the%20bold%20word%20from%20the%20Lord%20enabled%20him%20to%20remain%20calm%2C%20relaxed%2C%20and%20confident.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20said%2C%20%22Do%20not%20throw%20away%20this%20confident%20trust%20in%20the%20Lord%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20happens.%20Remember%20the%20great%20reward%20it%20brings%20you!%22%20(Hebrews%2010%3A35).%20And%20that%20reward%20is%20a%20%22faith%20that%20assures%20our%20salvation%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%2039).%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20the%20battle%20seems%20overwhelming%2C%20what%20choice%20do%20you%20have%20but%20to%20stand%20firm%3F%20If%20you%20turn%20and%20run%20from%20the%20enemy%2C%20you%20will%20not%20stand%20at%20all.%20Burn%20the%20retreat%20bridge!%20Your%20only%20option%20is%20to%20stand-and%20when%20you%20do%2C%20God%20will%20fight%20for%20you!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
